{"info": {"author": "Francis Gassert", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# xlPandas\n\nRead and write Excel xlsx using pandas/openpyxl without destroying formatting.\n\nSometimes you have a nicely formatted worksheet, but you'd like to work with it\nusing [pandas](https://pypi.org/project/pandas/), or perhaps you want to write\ndata to an Excel template.\n\nPandas can read and write Excel files using `xlrd`, but treats them like csvs.\nxlPandas uses [openpyxl](https://pypi.org/project/openpyxl/) to access data\nwhile preserving template formatting, macros, and other worksheet attributes.\n\n## Install\n\n`pip install xlpandas`\n\n## Example\n\n``` python\n\nimport xlpandas as xpd\n\n# Read excel file\ndf = xpd.read_file('template.xlsx', skiprows=2)\nprint(df.columns)\n\n# Modify dataframe\ndf['new_column'] = True\n\n# Access openpyxl worksheet\nsheet = df.to_sheet()\nsheet.cell(1,1).value = 'title'\n\n# From openpyxl worksheet\ndf = xpd.xlDataFrame(sheet)\n\n# Write file\ndf.to_file('out.xlsx')\n\n```\n\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/fgassert/xlpandas", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "xlpandas", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/xlpandas/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/xlpandas/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/fgassert/xlpandas"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/xlpandas/0.1.3/", "requires_dist": ["openpyxl", "pandas"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Read and write xlsx/xlst using pandas/openpyxl while preserving Excel formatting", "version": "0.1.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>xlPandas</h1>\n<p>Read and write Excel xlsx using pandas/openpyxl without destroying formatting.</p>\n<p>Sometimes you have a nicely formatted worksheet, but you'd like to work with it\nusing <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/pandas/\" rel=\"nofollow\">pandas</a>, or perhaps you want to write\ndata to an Excel template.</p>\n<p>Pandas can read and write Excel files using <code>xlrd</code>, but treats them like csvs.\nxlPandas uses <a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/openpyxl/\" rel=\"nofollow\">openpyxl</a> to access data\nwhile preserving template formatting, macros, and other worksheet attributes.</p>\n<h2>Install</h2>\n<p><code>pip install xlpandas</code></p>\n<h2>Example</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"nn\">xlpandas</span> <span class=\"k\">as</span> <span class=\"nn\">xpd</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Read excel file</span>\n<span class=\"n\">df</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">xpd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">read_file</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'template.xlsx'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">skiprows</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">df</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">columns</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Modify dataframe</span>\n<span class=\"n\">df</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s1\">'new_column'</span><span class=\"p\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"kc\">True</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Access openpyxl worksheet</span>\n<span class=\"n\">sheet</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">df</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_sheet</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"n\">sheet</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">cell</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"s1\">'title'</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># From openpyxl worksheet</span>\n<span class=\"n\">df</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">xpd</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">xlDataFrame</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">sheet</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Write file</span>\n<span class=\"n\">df</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">to_file</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'out.xlsx'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6545791, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2d7a4e947139b446e4cf5f43e30e1d3c", "sha256": "53b459d00b7b9caf580d3cc3fddc4997eff844b3e07bbfc531be827a31335998"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "xlpandas-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2d7a4e947139b446e4cf5f43e30e1d3c", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3914, "upload_time": "2019-12-24T19:34:02", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-12-24T19:34:02.783078Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/0d/c1/aba3791749feb956a062f434d5f95fd5d4151052a4a6beef1cb9ef07d144/xlpandas-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "c65695e611a3bd49072cd70c6863b067", "sha256": "eb15221afbc2ee4a73a28179bea38781777f654f18405ec1851dd8d60f59b37d"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "xlpandas-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "c65695e611a3bd49072cd70c6863b067", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2754, "upload_time": "2019-12-24T19:34:05", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-12-24T19:34:05.348569Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/66/12/9c5c8c8532753b5638cf8a0c9afed82e49deb57b0733171020359ec0d456/xlpandas-0.1.0.tar